menu "Ainekio platform"

config AINEKIO_PIN_MAP_B
    bool "Use Freenove N16R8 MAP_B board-only servo remap"
    default y
    help
        Builds the Freenove ESP32-S3 N16R8 allocation with all eight servo
        outputs on exposed GPIOs. GPIO0 and GPIO43 hand off their boot-time
        roles to the OLED I2C bus; GPIO47 and GPIO48 drive servos R4 and R3.

config AINEKIO_PHYSICAL_MOTION_ENABLED
    bool "Enable all eight servo outputs and semantic motion"
    default y
    help
        Enables all eight MAP_B servo outputs after platform initialization and
        permits normal semantic motion plus calibration commands. Startup keeps
        the 20 ms channel stagger and reduced-range safety profile; the pin-map
        guard rejects any future servo assignment on N16R8 PSRAM GPIO33-37.

config AINEKIO_MOTION_RANGE_PERCENT
    int "Initial motion range around logical center (percent)"
    range 10 100
    default 25
    help
        Scales every platform motion target around logical center 90 degrees.
        The default maps the source 0-180 degree range to 67.5-112.5 degrees.
        Raise only after the installed linkage limits are calibrated.

config AINEKIO_MOTION_MIN_FRAME_MS
    int "Minimum platform motion frame duration (milliseconds)"
    range 20 1000
    default 100
    help
        Prevents imported motion frames from commanding the initial reduced
        range faster than this duration.

config AINEKIO_SERVO_STARTUP_STAGGER_MS
    int "Delay between enabling servo channels at startup (milliseconds)"
    range 0 200
    default 20
    help
        Enables the eight centered 50 Hz outputs sequentially to reduce the
        instantaneous current step, following the Sesame firmware pattern.

config AINEKIO_BATTERY_MONITOR_ENABLED
    bool "Enable the GPIO3 battery divider and cutoff monitor"
    default y
    help
        Samples the planned 100k/47k divider on GPIO3, reports battery voltage,
        and applies the configured warning, cutoff, and recovery guards. H9
        refines the ADC correction against a multimeter; it does not gate
        initial monitoring.

config AINEKIO_MIC_SLOT_RIGHT
    bool "INMP441 drives the right I2S slot"
    default n
    help
        Select this only when the microphone L/R strap is wired for the right
        channel. The default reads the left slot and must be verified at H2/H4.

config AINEKIO_SSD1306_ADDRESS
    hex "SSD1306 7-bit I2C address"
    range 0x3c 0x3d
    default 0x3c
    help
        The common SSD1306 module address. H2 must verify the installed display;
        display initialization failure never blocks the control runtime.

config AINEKIO_BATTERY_DIVIDER_FACTOR
    string "Battery divider ratio"
    default "3.12766"
    help
        Planned ratio for the Parts Overview's 100k upper and 47k lower divider.
        H9 still measures the installed divider and stores ADC calibration.

endmenu
